g.text: UML Diagram: Class ClassificationItem in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.

a.title: ― ClassificationItemPosition: Provides a classification item with an index conveying the order of the classification item within a sequence, expressed as an integer, progressing upward from 0 or 1.
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationItemPosition: Provides a classification item with an index conveying the order of the classification item within a sequence, expressed as an integer, progressing upward from 0 or 1.

a.title: ― AuthorizationSource: Identifies the authorizing agency and allows for the full text of the authorization (law, regulation, or other form of authorization).
a.xlink:title: ― AuthorizationSource: Identifies the authorizing agency and allows for the full text of the authorization (law, regulation, or other form of authorization).

a.title: ― StatisticalClassification: Set of categories represented by classification items where the subset of immediate children categories for any given parent category are mutually exclusive and jointly exhaustive with respect to that parent.
a.xlink:title: ― StatisticalClassification: Set of categories represented by classification items where the subset of immediate children categories for any given parent category are mutually exclusive and jointly exhaustive with respect to that parent.

a.title: ― Level: Set of all classification items the same number of relationships from the root (or top) classification item.
a.xlink:title: ― Level: Set of all classification items the same number of relationships from the root (or top) classification item.

a.title: ― Category: Concept whose role is to define and measure a characteristic.
a.xlink:title: ― Category: Concept whose role is to define and measure a characteristic.

a.title: ― ClassificationItemRelationship: Source-target relationship between classification items in a classification item relation structure.
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationItemRelationship: Source-target relationship between classification items in a classification item relation structure.

a.title: ― Notation: Representation of a category in the context of a code or a classification item, as opposed of the corresponding instance value which would appear when used in a dataset.
a.xlink:title: ― Notation: Representation of a category in the context of a code or a classification item, as opposed of the corresponding instance value which would appear when used in a dataset.

a.title: ― IndividualMember: Distinct element that is not itself a collection (atomic).
a.xlink:title: ― IndividualMember: Distinct element that is not itself a collection (atomic).

a.title: ― Sign: Something that suggests the presence or existence of a fact, condition, or quality.
a.xlink:title: ― Sign: Something that suggests the presence or existence of a fact, condition, or quality.

a.title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...

a.title: ― ObjectName: A standard means of expressing a name for a class object. A linguistic signifier. Human understandable name (word, phrase, or mnemonic) that reflects the ISO/IEC 11179-5 naming principles.

a.title: ― DateRange: Expresses a date/time range using a start date and end date (both with the structure of Date and supporting the use of ISO and non-ISO date structures). Use in all locations where a range of dates is required, i.e. validFor, embargoPeriod, collectionPeriod, etc.
